catch `Error` for unsupported cases. There could be nuances in how exceptions behave in native images. I'll need to investigate this carefully to avoid issues.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating dynamic class loading**\\n\\nI think I need to ensure I wrap only the `Error` without skipping it. When using `new URLClassLoader`, it may throw an `UnsupportedFeatureError` if there's an issue, and a `ClassNotFoundException` if the JAR isn't present. The rule specifies that I catch `Error`, which is good. I’m considering whether I need to add a test for active class loading. My approach involves using reflection, and I wonder if this dynamic loading for ordinary reflection is even necessary in this case. I’ll go for it.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering dynamic access and testing**\\n\\nI’m wondering if the coverage report might need to analyze additional dynamic access, but I’m not sure if that's ideal. The external dynamic report only considers active classes. I could create a runner class in a child loader to call `FactoryHelper.typeIndex(Boolean.TYPE)` and invoke `Runnable.run` from the parent interface. However, this still requires dynamic class loading and potentially a new instance, which complicates things. \\n\\nInstead, I might consider using `java.net.URLClassLoader` and avoiding `ServiceLoader`. I think adding a test called `isolatedLoaderRunsFactoryHelperInitializationPath` is a good move, especially since the method order isn't guaranteed. It should load a separate `FactoryHelper`, trigger initialization, and then use reflection to invoke the public method while catching `Error`. Plus, I must remember to close `URLClassLoader` using try-with-resources. If there's a null parent, it may only load the Java bootstrap, but I’m noticing that the `SecurityActions` class is in the same JAR loaded by the child, and I might not need to use `Javassist` exceptions statically. That’s some progress!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying class loading and dependencies**\\n\\nI’m realizing that if the parent is null, it won't see the test classes, but that's not a big issue since it can still load `javassist` from the URL. I’m considering that my code source path might be the classes directory, and for the dependency JAR, it’s likely a JAR URL. If it’s a Gradle native test on the classpath, it may be the actual JAR. Under the JVM, if the parent is null, I can use `Class.forName(\\\"javassist.util.proxy.FactoryHelper\\\", true, loader)` to load from the URL, and the `SecurityActions` for `System.getSecurityManager` looks fine too.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_0J2XLjrrNHaozyySPTZTiFOS|fc_093d513f616c7a9d0169f51817baa081a289d8f1567702ea7e", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/javassist/javassist/3.12.0.GA/src/test/java/javassist_javassist/FactoryHelperTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.io.ByteArrayInputStream;\nimport java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;\nimport java.io.DataOutputStream;\n\nimport javassist.ClassPool;\n", "newText": "import java.io.ByteArrayInputStream;\nimport java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;\nimport java.io.DataOutputStream;\nimport java.lang.reflect.Method;\nimport java.net.URL;\nimport java.net.URLClassLoader;\n\nimport javassist.ClassPool;\n"}, {"oldText": "    @Test\n    void bridgeExercisesClassLookupHelper() throws Exception {\n", "newText": "    @Test\n    void isolatedLoaderRunsFactoryHelperInitializationPath() throws Exception {\n        try {\n            URL javassistLocation = FactoryHelper.class.getProtectionDomain().getCodeSource().getLocation();\n            try (URLClassLoader loader = new URLClassLoader(new URL[] { javassistLocation }, null)) {\n                Class<?> isolatedFactoryHelper = Class.forName(FactoryHelper.class.getName(), true, loader);\n                Method typeIndex = isolatedFactoryHelper.getMethod(\"typeIndex\", Class.class);\n\n                assertThat(typeIndex.invoke(null, Boolean.TYPE)).isEqualTo(0);\n            }\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            verifyUnsupportedDynamicClassLoading(error);\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void bridgeExercisesClassLookupHelper() throws Exception {\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2162, "output": 3034, "cacheRead": 35840, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 41036, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777670123439, "responseId": "resp_093d513f616c7a9d0169f517ebfe8881a297ac8dc3e1a19ef3"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_0J2XLjrrNHaozyySPTZTiFOS|fc_093d513f616c7a9d0169f51817baa081a289d8f1567702ea7e", "toolName": "edit", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully replaced 2 block(s) in tests/src/javassist/javassist/3.12.0.GA/src/test/java/javassist_javassist/FactoryHelperTest.java."}], "details": {"diff": "     ...\n   8 \n   9 import java.io.ByteArrayInputStream;\n  10 import java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;\n  11 import java.io.DataOutputStream;\n+ 12 import java.lang.reflect.Method;\n+ 13 import java.net.URL;\n+ 14 import java.net.URLClassLoader;\n  12 \n  13 import javassist.ClassPool;\n  14 import javassist.CtClass;\n  15 import javassist.bytecode.AccessFlag;\n     ...\n  28 public class FactoryHelperTest {\n  29     private static final String BRIDGE_CLASS_NAME = \"javassist.util.proxy.FactoryHelperCoverageBridge\";\n  30 \n  31     @Test\n+ 35     void isolatedLoaderRunsFactoryHelperInitializationPath() throws Exception {\n+ 36         try {\n+ 37             URL javassistLocation = FactoryHelper.class.getProtectionDomain().getCodeSource().getLocation();\n+ 38             try (URLClassLoader loader = new URLClassLoader(new URL[] { javassistLocation }, null)) {\n+ 39                 Class<?> isolatedFactoryHelper = Class.forName(FactoryHelper.class.getName(), true, loader);\n+ 40                 Method typeIndex = isolatedFactoryHelp